Yes we have been. Like any &quot;end-game&quot; big guild we hunger to kill big mobs, or we just get bored with EQ and quit for DAoC or whatever. As Seliak mentioned, however, Doze is really the only &quot;juicy&quot; mob that we consistantly find up, so when we do find it up, we try to kill it. Sure, after any given server patch we could go kill other big mobs that spawn at patch, but the only others that many guildies still need loot from are VS and Trak, but we only kill a small portion of these 2 mobs due to a deal we are a part of with 15 or so other big guilds of EMarr.<br>
<br>
