<br>
<br>
Issue 2: DG fucking up UI's Doze fight<br>
<br>
The facts as they are:<br>
<br>
A DG guy opened the door to NToV while UI was in HoT. He was killed quickly just south of the door, and 2 NToV wyverns also stayed on the South side of the door.<br>
<br>
Golgar and Blazestorm joked about training UI in say at zone in with a UI guy right there.<br>
<br>
As UI was fighting Doze and Gailen stood outside the HoT, the door to HoT opened and center area mobs aggrod UI.<br>
<br>
UI was not happy about this turn of events and confronted Golgar, a DG officer, who in turn responded confrontationally rather than appologetically.<br>
<br>
NToV mobs aggrod on UI as they were undergoing their CR the bulk of their raid force (and incedentally also on DG as they attempted to CR Gailen).<br>
<br>
Now given all that, the obvious conclusion is that DG conspired to purposefully repeatedly train UI and prevent them from killing Doze. I can totally understand how UI and most people who read this board came to that conclusion, and I know that if the positions were reversed, we would be damn pissed at UI. But as it turns out, I also know for a fact that this was not a purposeful train by DG - the problem is that I know my guildmates and I know in my heart that they couldn't do this, but don't have screenshots to prove this.<br>
<br>
I now see that Gailen denies even opening the door, and I believe that 100%. It's possible that CoV mobs happened to pick that moment to aggro KoS UI player(s) inside HoT and opened the door themselves (I have seen some screwy stuff like that in there, and tried to find who to yell at for opening the door and found nobody). It's possible that a UI player inside ToV got dangerously close to the door and/or accidentally opened it. It's possible that Gailen accidentally opened the door somehow without even realizing it. I know full well that all such explanations do sound extremely unlikely, but Gailen lying sounds far less likely to me.<br>
<br>
So, at the very least, we screwed up by even being there so that we could be blamed. And for not warning UI about the NToV mobs that we accidentally released (but I agree with that guy who said he found it hard to believe they stayed out there that long - I didn't even begin to think that it would be a problem later, but live and learn, now I know better). And the jokes about training proved to be in very bad form in hindsight after all this shit happened - I agree that it sure makes DG look guilty as hell. And personally I don't think that Golgar's confrontational reaction in OOC or on this board did anybody any good and should be apologized for - even though he was pissed because he knew the accusations of intentional training were false, he should have seen how UI could reach that conclusion and reacted constructively. He said he does not &quot;control&quot; all guildies meaning that he did not &quot;order&quot; Gailen to train UI, but everybody is right in that as an officer he does bear some responsibility, for punishment (if necessasary) after the fact if nothing else.<br>
<br>
And again, I don't know who's CR efforts aggrod those NToV mobs first, UI's or DG's, from all I heard it still could have been either, but it's our fault they were there even if we assumed they were long gone.<br>
<br>
However, it is kinda funny to me that people who know Gailen are so ready to believe that he obviously became demonspew after joining DG. No way was Gailen &quot;ordered&quot; to train UI. Even if you don't believe that, you have to know that no way would he even think of carrying out such an evil order. Seriously. Before I just assumed that maybe Gailen had a serious brain fart and opened the door to run into HoT to track things for a second or something, but now I see that he denies opening the door, so I believe him 100% (can't rule out the extremely small chance that he somehow clicked on it accidentally without even knowing, though).<br>
<br>
<br>
